An ROC curve was generated comparing the radiologists reading of pneumonia on the original films (i.e., gold standard), digital camera, and film digitizer. The value for the area under the curve was 0.86 (95% CI = 0.78–0.95) for the digital camera and 0.91 (95% CI = 0.87–0.95) for the film digitizer (Figure 1
). There was no statistically significant difference between the two curves (p
 = 0.29). The cost of the film digitizer was $3000; the camera and tripod cost $965.
